data.description: Discover the epitome of coastal living in this meticulously renovated 3-bedroom, 2-bath residence with a bonus room and a two-car carport is nestled in the exclusive Tropical Shores community, this home offers an unparalleled lifestyle with access to the private marina, boat slips, and a community center along the Intercoastal Waterway on the shore of Little Sarasota Bay. Great boating access with no fixed bridges, short boat ride to Midnight Pass, Turtle Beach, Siesta Key. This costal residence has been extensively renovated including luxury vinyl plank throughout house, kitchen was updated and expanded in 2020 with beautiful high end white cabinetry with an abundance of storage, counter to ceiling backsplash, stainless steel appliances. Major structural item updates include Roof 2022, new septic tank 2023, new cistern tank 2023, and drain field in 2023, Block construction, A/C 2018, interior laundry area off the kitchen with new tankless water heater. The open floor plan boasts lots of natural light. Plus Florida room provides ample space for family gatherings and the split bedroom floor plan gives great privacy. The primary suite boasts a huge walk-in closet and an ensuite bathroom with a walk-in shower. Spacious guest bedrooms share a tastefully updated bathroom. Exterior highlights included new outdoor landscaping, huge brick paver patio off the back of the home with a deck. Perfect place to entertain family and friends in the fully fenced and private backyard. The front yard features a beautiful, paved walkway, ample parking for your boat and vehicles. The flood zone X500 does not require flood insurance while being only a couple blocks from the water. This property’s location in South Sarasota is ideal. Within a half mile to Costco, Sprouts, Target, and Publix. Numerous local restaurants and medical services nearby. A short 10-minute drive to award-winning Siesta Key Beach. The community is non-deed restricted with no mandatory HOA fees. Membership in the neighborhood association allows access to amenities. Current rates: $75 per family member, $300 for boat ramp access, and $1100 annually for a boat slip. Don’t miss your chance to own in this incredible West of the Trail location! Schedule your private showing today. ** 3D tour and Video attached to listing. No home inspection was completed by previous buyer they just had a change of heart**
